We have found this hymn nowhere save in F, where it follows the Gloria in excelsis. It has been recently printed by Dreves in his Analecta fflmni medii aeui, xix. 2363 following him, we have entitled it “De SS. The monastery in which the manuscript F was written may have been dedicated to St. Peter and St. Paul, such a dedication being common in Ireland as in Englaud. Petri et Pauli '’; there was a monastery with the same dedication at Annagh³; and on Saint's lsland in Lough Derg the Augustinian priory of St. Peter and St. Paul was on the site of an old foundation.
